steps.description:
What makes Final Fantasy XI so appealing to you? Is it the fact that it has different continents that you will never go to? Is it the fighting? Whatever it is, try to minimize this happiness in FFXI, and make it a pleasure that you could also get in every day life. Take a martial arts class. Many gamers are very interested in the martial arts, but never study it. Take up some sort of martial art that is similar to your character in FFXI. For example, if you use a sword in the game, then take up fencing, Kendo, or SCA fighting. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/05/Break-a-Final-Fantasy-XI-Addiction-Step-3Bullet1-Version-2.jpg/v4-460px-Break-a-Final-Fantasy-XI-Addiction-Step-3Bullet1-Version-2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/0/05/Break-a-Final-Fantasy-XI-Addiction-Step-3Bullet1-Version-2.jpg/aid208005-v4-728px-Break-a-Final-Fantasy-XI-Addiction-Step-3Bullet1-Version-2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":288,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"455","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Try Reading. Novels have just as much excitement and adventure as FFXI, but you can expand other skills -- such as critical thinking and vocabulary -- in addition to those that interactive storytelling and game play will build. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2d/Break-a-Final-Fantasy-XI-Addiction-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Break-a-Final-Fantasy-XI-Addiction-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/2/2d/Break-a-Final-Fantasy-XI-Addiction-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/aid208005-v4-728px-Break-a-Final-Fantasy-XI-Addiction-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":288,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"455","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Play a different videogame. Sure, you might just find yourself in another addiction, but at least you're not paying every month. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4d/Break-a-Final-Fantasy-XI-Addiction-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Break-a-Final-Fantasy-XI-Addiction-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/4/4d/Break-a-Final-Fantasy-XI-Addiction-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/aid208005-v4-728px-Break-a-Final-Fantasy-XI-Addiction-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":288,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"455","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
